	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Bargynn spawns in the basment (down the hole).<BR>
Directions:<BR>
If the hole drops you into a small room:<BR>
Head down the passage out of the room till you find a stip of water going across the hall way.  Jump accross the water and take a left down a set of stairs.  Once down the stairs you'll have water on your right side a passage going forward and a passage to the left.  Take the left hand passage and you'll find a lake in front of you and accross the water 2 passage ways.  The passage ways are acctually 2 sides of the same room so just swim accross and your there.  Bargynn spawns in the middle of the room. <BR>
<BR>
If the hole drops you into a hallway:<BR>
You should drop right next to a stream of water.  Head down the hallway away from the water.  The passage way will open up and you'll have some water on your left hand side a set of stairs in front of you and a passage on your right headed back.  Take this passage and you'll be at a lake.  The two passages you see on the other side both lead to Bargynns spawn point. <BR>
<BR>
Hints on takeing him down.<BR>
When you head across the lake hop up onto the shore and stay right along the edge.  Everything here has a small agro radius (like the rest of kurns tower) so you'll probably aggro one mob at the most.  Kill the mobs in the passage your in should be 2 or 3.  You may want to wait a second to insure you killed the mob that roams around the area.  Now you just have Bargynn his 2 buddies and the mob thats hideing right behind the corner.  I'd recomend pulling the mob thats hideing and killing it then pulling Bargynn and his buddies.  Bargynn is around lvl 20 or so (yellow to me at 19) and I belive is a Shadow Knight though I'm not postive on this.   He drops his torch as his common drop and his claws as his rare drop.<BR>
<BR>
Well that should be everything you need to know to take out the big bad badger Bargynn.  Good hunting.<BR>
<BR>
Umarth<BR>
Elemoth Agarwean<BR>
Tallon Zek
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
